Shareholders of Messerschmitt-Boelkow-Blohm G.m.b.
H. postponed their formal endorsement of a merger with Daimler-Benz AG until another meeting on Nov. 17. 

The owners of the defense and aerospace concern, which include three regional states, several industrial companies and banks, met Friday to discuss the final terms of the transaction, in which Daimler-Benz will acquire 50.01% of 

But agreement aparently couldn't be reached because of opposition from the states of Hamburg and Bremen, which are demanding more influence over the German Airbus operations and a better guarantee against job losses in the troubled Northern German region. 

The two states and the state of Bavaria still hold a majority in MBB, but their stake will fall to around 30% after Daimler-Benz acquires its stake in the concern. 

